  <name>Notepad++ Qt</name>
  <summary>Native Linux Qt6 port of Notepad++</summary>
  <developer_name>clip52</developer_name>
  <description>
    <p>
      Notepad++ Qt is a native Linux port of the popular Notepad++ text editor,
      rebuilt on top of Qt6 and the bundled Scintilla and Lexilla editing
      components.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is the foundational (M1) release: the focus is on establishing a
      working Qt6 application, the core editor surface, and a clean Fedora
      packaging baseline.
    </p>
    <p>
      Plugin compatibility with the original Win32 Notepad++ plugins is
      intentionally dropped. A Qt-native plugin model is planned for future
      milestones — see docs/PORTING.md in the source tree.
    </p>
  </description>
  <categories>
    <category>Development</category>
    <category>TextEditor</category>
    <category>Utility</category>
  </categories>
